BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 157.20000000000002 670 Td (The Skeletal System: Your Frame) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 580 Td (Your skeleton is made up of 206 bones that give your body shape, protect) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 562 Td (your organs, and help you move. When you were born, you had about 270) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 544 Td (bones! Many fused together as you grew. Bones are alive - they grow, heal) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 526 Td (when broken, and make new blood cells inside their marrow. The smallest) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 508 Td (bone is in your ear \(size of a rice grain\). The largest is your thigh bone) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F1 11 Tf 72 490 Td (\(femur\).) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
